{"parentUuid":"aa66f40c-8778-4701-a266-2c4745e424f9","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EpnJDiPprJp34AXxHi6Xfy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's what was built and why each choice matters:\n\n**Null conversion via `v-model.nullable`**\n\nNuxt UI v4 components (`UInput`, `UTextarea`) support the `.nullable` modifier natively. When the field is cleared, instead of emitting `\"\"`, the component emits `null`. This is the key difference from plain Vue — you don't need a computed getter/setter or a Zod transform.\n\n`UInputNumber` already emits `null` natively when the field is cleared, so no modifier is needed there.\n\n**Zod schema**\n```ts\nnickname: z.string().nullable().optional()\nbio:      z.string().nullable().optional()\nage:      z.number().nullable().optional()\n```\n`.nullable()` allows `null`, `.optional()` allows `undefined` — together they cover the cleared-field case correctly.\n\n**Key fields summary:**\n\n| Field | Component | v-model | Null on empty |\n|-------|-----------|---------|---------------|\n| name | `UInput` | `v-model` | N/A (required) |\n| nickname | `UInput` | `v-model.nullable` | `null` |\n| bio | `UTextarea` | `v-model.nullable` | `null` |\n| age | `UInputNumber` | `v-model` | `null` (built-in) |\n\nThe JSON debug panel below the form makes it easy to verify `null` vs `\"\"` as you type and clear each field."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2230,"cache_read_input_tokens":16287,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2230,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZok3spDcvm9toK4kRGvZ","type":"assistant","uuid":"b88358df-63c2-45a3-a542-9c5953e4b1e5","timestamp":"2026-04-07T04:00:38.957Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/vercel/sandbox","sessionId":"a837875b-e5fe-40